{{see|eve}}

==English==

===Etymology===
Greek [[Εύα]] (Eva) is an adaption of the biblical Hebrew female name [[חוה|חַוָּה]] (Hawah) meaning 'life; lively; giving life'.
There is real Greek translation of the Hebrew name Hava: Ζωή ([[Zoe]]), meaning 'life, existence'.
The Hebrew male equivalent is היימ ([[Chaim]], [[Haim]]).

===Proper noun===
'''Eve'''

# according to the [[Bible]] and [[Qur'an]], the first [[woman]] and [[mother]] of the [[human race]]; [[Adam]]'s [[wife]]

